This paper deals with the problem of teaching robots how to perform tasks based on user preferences, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach presented in the paper relies on data gathered from crowdsourcing, which involves human-computer interaction and user studies, making it relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The method also involves machine learning techniques such as collaborative filtering and spectral clustering, which are common in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
